cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Backpropagate: Headless LLM fine-tuning on a single consumer GPU"
message: "If you use Backpropagate in published work, please cite both the software and the underlying SLAO research paper (see references)."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "MCP Tool Shop authors"
    email: 64996768+mcp-tool-shop@users.noreply.github.com
repository-code: "https://github.com/mcp-tool-shop-org/backpropagate"
url: "https://mcp-tool-shop-org.github.io/backpropagate/"
# version + date-released are kept in lockstep with pyproject.toml's [project].version
# and the matching CHANGELOG.md section. Update both fields at release time
# (Dependabot does not bump CFF). The pre-release coordinator script
# scripts/prep_release.sh (landed v1.4 Wave 6a, CIDOCS-F-025) bumps both
# fields from pyproject.toml's [project].version + the current UTC date
# and validates the references: list before the publish chain runs.
version: 1.3.0
date-released: 2026-05-24
license: MIT
keywords:
  - llm
  - fine-tuning
  - lora
  - qlora
  - unsloth
  - training
  - machine-learning
  - headless
  - api
# DOI: placeholder. Mint a Zenodo DOI on the v1.3.0 GitHub release and replace
# this comment with `doi: 10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXX`. See the Zenodo-GitHub
# integration docs at https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/archiving-a-github-repository/referencing-and-citing-content
references:
  - type: article
    title: "Merge before Forget: A Single LoRA Continual Learning via Continual Merging"
    authors:
      - family-names: "Qiao"
      - family-names: "Mahdavi"
    url: "https://arxiv.org/abs/2512.23017"
    year: 2025
    notes: "SLAO (Single LoRA Continual Learning via Asymmetric Merging) — the merge-between-runs technique that backpropagate's multi_run.py + slao.py implement to prevent catastrophic forgetting during extended fine-tuning campaigns. arXiv:2512.23017 is the primary citation; backpropagate is the paper's first known downstream adopter."
  - type: article
    title: "LoRA Learns Less and Forgets Less"
    authors:
      - family-names: "Biderman"
    url: "https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.09673"
    year: 2024
    notes: "Empirical evidence that LoRA at correct configuration matches full fine-tuning quality on most post-training tasks at 67% of the compute. Drives backpropagate's v1.3 default LoRA configuration (rank 256, all-linear target)."
  - type: article
    title: "LoRA: Low-Rank Adaptation of Large Language Models"
    authors:
      - family-names: "Hu"
      - family-names: "Shen"
      - family-names: "Wallis"
      - family-names: "Allen-Zhu"
      - family-names: "Li"
      - family-names: "Wang"
      - family-names: "Wang"
      - family-names: "Chen"
    url: "https://arxiv.org/abs/2106.09685"
    year: 2021
    notes: "Foundational LoRA paper underpinning the entire library."
